''Beyond Thirty'' (later republished as ''The Lost Continent'') is a 1916 science fiction novel by . It was originally published in serial form in ''All Around Magazine''.
The novel, set in the year 2137, was heavily influenced by the events of . In the future world depicted in the novel, Europe has descended into barbarism while an   remains sheltered from the destruction. The title ''Beyond Thirty'' refers to the degree of  that inhabitants of the Western Hemisphere are forbidden to pass.
